hints.description: This company is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that primarily owns, operates, and develops apartment communities. They focus on high-quality, professionally managed properties in desirable locations across the United States, catering to a range of renters. ***** is one of the largest apartment owners in the nation, known for its focus on resident experience and community amenities.
hints.funFact1: The company was formed in 1997 as a spin-off from *****, a major insurance and financial services company, allowing it to focus solely on the apartment sector.
hints.funFact2: *****s portfolio includes properties with unique features like rooftop terraces, dog parks, and even resident-exclusive co-working spaces, reflecting a commitment to attracting and retaining modern renters.
